**I detected memory leak in the spine after replace scene.**

- cocos2d-x version: 3.13.1
- devices test on: Win10
- developing environments
   - VS version: 2015
   - OS: Win10

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Create two scenes with Skeleton Animations
2. Load first scene with animation
3. Replaced by the second scene with animation. Watch mtmory

**My solution:**

I changed next file: `cocos2d\cocos\editor-support\spine\SkeletonBatch.cpp`

```
SkeletonBatch::SkeletonBatch ()
    {
        _firstCommand = new Command();
        _command = _firstCommand;

       // comment next code <---------------------------
        //Director::getInstance()->getEventDispatcher()->addCustomEventListener(EVENT_AFTER_DRAW_RESET_POSITION, [this](EventCustom* eventCustom){
        //    this->update(0);
        //});;

       // restore code from last version <---------------------------
		Director::getInstance()->getScheduler()->scheduleUpdate(this, -1, false);
    }

    SkeletonBatch::~SkeletonBatch () {
       // comment next code <---------------------------
        //Director::getInstance()->getEventDispatcher()->removeCustomEventListeners(EVENT_AFTER_DRAW_RESET_POSITION);

       // restore code from last version <---------------------------
		Director::getInstance()->getScheduler()->unscheduleUpdate(this);

        Command* command = _firstCommand;
        while (command) {
            Command* next = command->next;
            delete command;
            command = next;
        }
    }

    void SkeletonBatch::update (float delta) {
        _command = _firstCommand;
    }

```

